The paper also involves mathematical proofs and analysis, which could place it in cs.MP or cs.DS. Additionally, the concavity theorem of Lieb has applications in computational complexity theory, which could make cs.CC a relevant sub-category. Finally, the paper does not involve any experimental work or implementation, which makes it less likely to belong to sub-categories such as cs.LG or cs.CV.
